f=Engineering/quinn/operational/agent/quinn-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration quinn, gate charter control point. · h2:Config Template=`# --- Charter (senior authority) --- \· security_charter_path: <FILL_IN>       # operator-adopted version; unadopted → most-restrictive mode \· plan_lock_log: <FILL_IN>               # Rail 1 append-only ledger (asset template) \· hash_algorithm: sha256                 # default; per charter-enforcement instruction 2 \· sandbox_policy: <FILL_IN>              # Rail 2 (charter config)` · in=`security_charter_path` most-restrictive mode department-wide: quinn issues plan-locks (so agent makes external calls), writes, red-team; affected output states this. `plan_lock_log` effect unadopted charter Rail locks recorded, external calls proceed. Unset `coverage_floors` `critical_flows` gate runs tier-presence assertions only, loudly labeled; quinn recommends values operator (labeled reasoning-based) never enforces invented numbers. Absent connectors browser gates degrade labeled manual checklists (browser-verification fallback); tier reports UNMET, never silently passes. · f=Unfilled config degrades loudly, never silently. charter's absence loudest degradation stops whole department's external tool use, design.